title: The Second World War - by Sir Winston Churchill
description:
Churchill&#039;s history of the Second World War is, and will remain, the definitive work. Lucid, dramatic, remarkable for its breadth and sweep and for its sense of personal involvement, it is universally acknowledged as a magnificent reconstruction.

this abridgement of his original 6 volume memoirs is 1088 pages

this recording narrated by Christian Rodska
approx 45 hours running time

broken into 4 parts:

1 Milestones to Disaster
2 Alone
3 The Grand Alliance
4 Triumph and Tragedy
